# Next.js Frontend Conventions

## App Router

- Use App Router exclusively (no Pages Router).
- Default to **Server Components**. Only add `"use client"` when you need browser APIs, state, or effects.
- Fetch data in async Server Components — avoid `useEffect` + `useState` for data fetching.
- Use `next/navigation` (not `next/router`).

## Route Groups

- `(auth)/` — public pages (login, register). No auth required.
- `(dashboard)/` — end-user shell. Must be authenticated. Contains `chat/`, `settings/`.
- `(admin)/` — admin shell. Must be `admin` or `developer` role. Contains `agents/`, `providers/`, `users/`, `analytics/`, `audit/`, `settings/`.

End users must never see admin routes. Redirect or show 403.

## Components

- File naming: `PascalCase.tsx` for components, `kebab-case.ts` for utilities/hooks.
- UI primitives come from `@centrai/ui` (shadcn/ui based). Don't create parallel primitives.
- Component structure: `components/chat/`, `components/admin/`, `components/layout/`, `components/ui/`.

```
// ✅ Component file structure
export function MessageBubble({ message }: MessageBubbleProps) {
  // ...
}
```

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS exclusively. No CSS modules, no styled-components.
- Use `cn()` utility (from `@centrai/ui`) for conditional classes.
- Dark mode via `class` strategy. Use `dark:` variants.

## State & Data

- Server state: fetch in Server Components or use React Query / SWR for client-side.
- Auth state: `useAuth()` hook from context provider.
- Chat streaming: `useChat()` hook using `fetch` POST + `ReadableStream` for SSE parsing.
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod resolver.

## Chat UI Specifics

- Agent/model picker shows only `published` agents and `enabled` models from API.
- Never expose system prompts, agent config details, or internal IDs to end users.
- Stream tokens via SSE (`text/event-stream` from POST response). Buffer and render incrementally.
- Render assistant messages with Markdown (react-markdown + syntax highlighting + KaTeX).

## Performance

- Use `loading.tsx` and `Suspense` for route-level loading states.
- Lazy-load heavy components (code editor, charts) with `dynamic()`.
- Images via `next/image` with proper `width`/`height` or `fill`.
